:h1 id='HELP_OPTIONS' res=11000 hide.Options
:lines  align=center.
:font facename='Helv' size=0x0.

:i1.Options
:color fc='DarkBlue' bc='default'.Options:color fc='Default' bc='Default'.
:elines.
:p.&PrgName. allows the user the configure several items. All setting will be
saved when you quit &PrgName..
:p.The following settings change the difficulty of the game. Set them according
to your 
:i1.Skills
skills. You will get more points when playing on a more difficult level.
:parml tsize=8 break=all.
:pt.
:i1.Speed
:hp2.Speed
:pd.:ehp2.Set the initial speed of &PrgName..
:pt.
:i1.Startlevel
:hp2.Startlevel
:pd.:ehp2.Set the startlevel. Each Level represents a randomly filled line
:eparml.
:p.General settings
:parml tsize=8 break=all.
:pt.
:i1.Sound
:hp2.Sound
:pd.:ehp2.Use this to disable sound-effects. This button will be ghosted if
&PrgName. can't play sounds on your system (eg. you have no sound-card
installed)
:pt.
:i1.Grid
:hp2.Grid
:pd.:ehp2.Enable/Disable the grid on the playfield. Very useful when dropping
pieces.
:pt.
:i1.Next Piece
:hp2.Next Piece
:pd.:ehp2.Display the next piece.
:pt.:hp2.Remain paused
:pd.:ehp2.If enabled &PrgName. will remain in pause-mode once you went into
pause-state. This occurs everytime you switch the focus to another than the
playing window (eg. switching to the desktop window, opening a &PrgName.
dialog).
:pt.
:i1.Palette
:hp2.Palette
:pd.:ehp2.Select a specific colormap. HINT : If you have already some pieces on
the playfield you can see the new color immediately.
:pt.
:i1.Solid color
:hp2.Solid color
:pd.:ehp2.Use only solid-colors. This may be useful if you have only 16
color-screen. &PrgName. will not try to mix colors from the system-palette.
:pt.
:eparml.
