:h1 id='HELP_DEFINE_KEYS' res=14000 hide.Define Keys
:lines  align=center.
:font facename='Helv' size=0x0.

:i1.Define Keys
:color fc='DarkBlue' bc='default'.Define Keys:color fc='Default' bc='Default'.
:elines.
:p.This dialog let's you define your own 
:i1.Key-bindings
key-bindings. Please note that there are some restriction when defining a key.
Follow these steps to redefine a key.
:p.
:ol.
:li. Select the funtion you would like to assign a new key by pressing the
appropriate button. The buttons have the following meaning :
:lp.:artwork  runin name='F:\Projects\STris\Graphics\left.bmp'.    Move Left
:lp.:artwork  runin name='F:\Projects\STris\Graphics\right.bmp'.    Move Right
:lp.:artwork  runin name='F:\Projects\STris\Graphics\drop.BMP'.    Drop
:lp.:artwork  runin name='F:\Projects\STris\Graphics\rotateLeft.BMP'.    Rotate
counterclockwise
:lp.:artwork  runin name='F:\Projects\STris\Graphics\rotateRight.BMP'.    Rotate
clockwise
:li. Press the desired key. Press the ESC-key to abort.
:note.Not all keys can be used (eg. space-Bar) you will see a message if you
press a key that is not supported.
:eol.
:p.
:p.Use the :hp2.Default :ehp2.Button to switch back to the standard keymap.
:p.
:p.
